abstract: WASHINGTON, Sept. 7. Private dispatches received here today confirm the news that California has elected the Republican ticket by a decided majority. There is still some doubt as to the Legislature, on which the political complexion of the next Senator depends. The general result, however, is accepted with great pleasure by Republicans, and was totally unanticipated by the Democrats. abstract: WASHINGTON, D.C., Sept. 19 1 A.M. The high barometer which was Sunday night central in Western Pennsylvania has extended southeastward to the Middle Atlantic coast, and fallen somewhat. A small area of low pressure has passed from Minnesota over Lake Michigan, and is now central between Huron and Ontario. The pressure has risen again from Kansas northward. Clear weather has prevailed on the Atlantic coast, excepting the cloudiness in North Carolina.
